IRI: https://w3id.org/arco/ontology/context-description/RelatedWorkSituation

This class represents a situation in which a cultural property is related to another work, that could even be another cultural property. Technical Characteristicc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/arco/ontology/denotative-description/TechnicalCharacteristic

This class represents a characteristic of a cultural property. For example it can represent a cultural property's particular costituent material or the technique with which it was made or its shape or color. Each technical characteristic is classified by a concept (i.e. "clay" is a techical characteristic classified by the technical concept "material" related to a cultural property). For each cultural property typology can be registered some specific technical characteristics.
Current version:
stable
Is defined by
https://w3id.org/arco/ontology/denotative-description
has super-classes
characteristic c
is in domain of
are available notes of op, is diapason of op, is extension of op, is file format of op, is filigree of op, is garment analysis of op, is garment colour of op, is included in technical status op, is mass storage of op, is material of op, is material or technique of op, is photo colour of op, is photo program of op, is photo size of op, is pixel dimension of op, is quality level of op, is resolution of op, is shape of op, is storage method or colour depth of op, is technical characteristic classified by op, is technical characteristic of op, is technique of op, is temperament of op, is tuning of op, is vibrating lenght of op
is in range of
classifies technical characteristic op, has available notes op, has diapason op, has extension op, has file format op, has filigree op, has garment analysis op, has garment colour op, has mass storage op, has material op, has material or technique op, has photo colour op, has photo program op, has photo size op, has pixel dimension op, has quality level op, has resolution op, has shape op, has storage method or colour depth op, has technical characteristic op, has technique op, has temperament op, has tuning op, has vibrating lenght op, includes technical characteristic op

Technical status of cultural entityc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/arco/ontology/denotative-description/CulturalEntityTechnicalStatus

This class represents the technical status of a cultural entity, that is a situation in which the cultural entity is associated to technical characteristics. The technical status has a temporal validity, related to the moment when the characteristics were observed. For instance, a cultural property techncal status is: "the cultural property X realized with pottery material and cylindrical in shape".
An example of usage of the class 'Cultural entity technical status' is the following: resource:CulturalEntityTechnicalStatus/0900281817-4 a a-dd:CulturalEntityTechnicalStatus ; rdfs:label "Technical status of cultural property 0900281817-4"@en ; a-dd:includesTechnicalCharacteristic resource:TechnicalCharacteristic/centinato, resource:TechnicalCharacteristic/stone-sculpture . resource:TechnicalCharacteristic/stone-sculpture a a-dd:TechnicalCharacteristic ; rdfs:label "stone/ sculpture" ; a-dd:isClassifiedBy a-dd:MaterialOrTechnique .
Current version:
stable
Is defined by
https://w3id.org/arco/ontology/denotative-description
has super-classes
situation c
is in domain of
includes technical characteristic op, is cultural entity technical status valid at op, is technical status of op, satisfies technical description op
is in range of
has technical status op, is cultural entity description satisfied by op, is included in technical status op, is time interval valid for op

This individual represents the techincal definition of textured fabrics of an ancient or contemporary garment, according to the standard provided by C.I.E.T.A., or laces. It can also represent the dinstrinction between plain fabric and textured fabric.

Temperamentni back to ToC or Named Individual ToC

IRI: https://w3id.org/arco/ontology/denotative-description/Temperament

This individual represents a musical instrument adopted temperament, especially in relation to an object in its original conditions, or after its restoration. For idiophones with fixed keys (e.g. xylophone, litophone, metallophone) the temperament represents the succession of intervals.
